# CODEOWNERS — auto-assigns reviewers based on changed paths.
# Docs: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Replace @your-username / @your-org/team-name with real GitHub handles.
# The last matching rule wins, so put more specific rules below general ones.

# ── Catch-all ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*                           @your-username

# ── Backend ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/Backend/                   @your-username

# ── Frontend ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/Frontend/                  @your-username

# ── Database migrations (high-risk — require explicit sign-off) ───────────────
/Backend/drizzle/migrations/ @your-username

# ── CI / GitHub config (changes here affect every contributor) ────────────────
/.github/                   @your-username
